    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I believe that this was actually already feasible, since we're calling `getFacetValues`, based on this https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-helper-js/blob/4bc11ed6b6db46b6e0ab3d567aebeed1658d1f83/dist/algoliasearch.helper.js#L8489-L8498\n\n> ``` js\n> //get values ordered only by name ascending using the string predicate\n> content.getFacetValues('city', {sortBy: ['name:asc']);\n> //get values  ordered only by count ascending using a function\n> content.getFacetValues('city', {\n>   sortBy: function(a, b) {\n>     return a.count - b.count;\n>   }\n> });\n> ```\n",
